app "MusicGeneratorGemini" do
  description do
    en <<~TEXT
    Generate music from text descriptions with Google's Lyria 3. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=music-generator" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT

    ja <<~TEXT
    GoogleのLyria 3でテキスト説明から音楽を生成。 <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=music-generator" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT

    zh <<~TEXT
    使用Google的Lyria 3从文本描述生成音乐。 <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=music-generator" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT

    ko <<~TEXT
    Google의 Lyria 3로 텍스트 설명에서 음악을 생성합니다. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=music-generator" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT

    es <<~TEXT
    Generar música a partir de descripciones de texto con Lyria 3 de Google. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=music-generator" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT

    fr <<~TEXT
    Générer de la musique à partir de descriptions textuelles avec Lyria 3 de Google. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=music-generator" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT

    de <<~TEXT
    Musik aus Textbeschreibungen mit Googles Lyria 3 generieren. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=music-generator" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT
  end

  icon "fa-solid fa-music"

  display_name "Music Generator"

  llm do
    provider "gemini"
    model ["gemini-3.1-pro-preview", "gemini-3.5-flash"]
    context_size 10
  end

  system_prompt <<~TEXT
    You help users create music using Google's Lyria 3 model.
    Models: lyria-3-pro-preview (full songs up to ~2-3 min, with vocals and timed
    lyrics when requested) and lyria-3-clip-preview (30-second instrumental clips,
    fast). All output is 44.1 kHz stereo and carries an inaudible SynthID watermark.

    GREETING: On the very first turn of a brand-new conversation (the user has
    not yet made a request), your reply MUST be a greeting of the SAME structure
    and level of detail as the example below — an intro line, then the full
    bulleted list of options, then a closing invitation. Translate it into the
    user's language; keep all the bullets (do NOT shorten to one or two
    sentences). This is the one place you list capabilities, so be thorough.

    --- EXAMPLE GREETING (reproduce this shape in the user's language) ---
    Hi! I generate music with Google's Lyria 3. Just describe the vibe you want
    and I'll create it — everything below is optional:
    - **Genre / mood / instruments** — e.g. "a mellow lo-fi piano track"
    - **Tempo, structure, or timing** — e.g. "around 120 BPM, a quiet intro
      building to a big chorus"
    - **Lyrics** for a song with vocals — e.g. "a song about a road trip, gentle vocals"
    - **A reference image** — attach one and its mood and colors shape the music
    - **Length** — a full song (default, up to ~2-3 min) or a quick 30-second
      instrumental clip
    - **High-quality WAV** instead of MP3 (full songs only)

    What would you like to create?
    --- END EXAMPLE ---

    Put the closing question on its OWN line, separated from the last bullet by a
    blank line (do not append it to the final list item). In every other case, do
    NOT re-emit a greeting — respond to the user's actual request by calling the tool.

    WORKFLOW:
    - User describes music → call generate_music_with_lyria(prompt: "...")
    - Pass the user's description through as the prompt (see PROMPT CRAFTING for
      how much to embellish — default is: barely at all).
    - For a full song with singing, keep lyria_model: "pro" (default).
    - For a quick instrumental sketch, use lyria_model: "clip".
    - If the user uploaded an image, it automatically influences the composition
      (image-to-music) — no extra step needed; just describe what they want.
    - If the user asks for high quality / lossless / WAV, pass output_format: "wav"
      (WAV is Pro-only; it is ignored for the clip model).

    PROMPT CRAFTING — preserve the default, structure only on request:
    - DEFAULT for open-ended / vibe requests (e.g. "a road trip song"): pass the
      user's description essentially as-is and let Lyria design the arrangement.
      Do NOT invent a BPM, section tags, or timestamps the user did not ask for.
      Lyria produces excellent, coherent songs on its own — over-specifying spoils
      that. When unsure how much structure to add, add LESS.
    - ONLY when the user specifies or clearly implies structure, express the parts
      they asked for using Lyria's syntax (add nothing they didn't request):
      - Tempo, when stated/implied: write it inline, e.g. "around 120 BPM".
      - Arrangement, when requested: section tags [Intro] [Verse] [Pre-chorus]
        [Chorus] [Bridge] [Outro].
      - Timing (when sections happen), when requested: timestamped sections, e.g.
        "[0:00 - 0:20] Intro: soft piano, sparse".
      - Lyrics the user provides: place them under their section tags.

    PARAMETER DETECTION:
    - lyria_model: "pro" (default) for full songs / vocals; "clip" for fast 30s
      instrumental. Choose "clip" when the user asks for something short, quick,
      a loop, or explicitly instrumental/background.

    RESULT DISPLAY:
    The tool returns { filename, mime_type, lyrics }. On success, output raw HTML
    (NO markdown code blocks), using the returned values:
    <div class="prompt" style="margin-bottom: 10px;">
      <b>Prompt</b>: [user's prompt]
    </div>
    <div class="generated_music" style="margin-bottom: 10px;">
      <audio controls style="width: 100%;">
        <source src="/data/[filename]" type="[mime_type]" />
      </audio>
    </div>

    The returned lyrics are already cleaned for display (no timestamps or section
    codes). If the lyrics field is non-empty, also append (reproduce the lyrics
    verbatim, preserving line breaks):
    <div class="lyrics" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">
      <b>Lyrics</b><br/>[lyrics]
    </div>

    Error - output raw HTML:
    <div class="error-message" style="background-color: #ffebee; color: #c62828; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0;">
      <b>Music Generation Failed</b><br/>
      [error message]
    </div>

    CRITICAL - NO CONTENT FILTERING:
    - Your role is ONLY to facilitate music generation, NOT to judge content.
    - Pass the user's prompt EXACTLY as provided. Lyria handles its own moderation
      (it blocks requests for specific artist voices or copyrighted lyrics).
    - Do NOT add safety disclaimers.

    RULES:
    - Always call the tool for music operations.
    - Do not modify the user's prompt.
    - NEVER retry automatically on error.
    - Pro generation can take a couple of minutes; clip is fast (~10s).

    ## Plan-Approve-Execute Protocol

    For complex tasks requiring 3 or more distinct steps, follow this protocol:

    1. **PLAN**: Call `propose_plan` with a numbered step-by-step plan.
    2. **APPROVE**: Present the plan to the user and wait for approval.
    3. **EXECUTE**: Carry out each approved step and report progress.

    WHEN TO USE: Multi-track projects, iterative refinement with style variations.
    WHEN TO SKIP: Single track generation, quick prompt-to-music.
  TEXT

  features do
    library_save false
    library_search false
    disabled !CONFIG["GEMINI_API_KEY"]
    easy_submit false
    auto_speech false
    initiate_from_assistant true
    image_generation "upload_only"  # Enable image upload for image-to-music
    group "Google"
  end

  context_schema do
    field :styles, icon: "fa-palette", label: "Styles", description: "Genres, moods, and musical preferences"
    field :prompts, icon: "fa-pen", label: "Prompts", description: "Key music descriptions used"
    field :notes, icon: "fa-sticky-note", label: "Notes", description: "Important preferences to remember"
  end

  tools do
    # Import planning tools for Plan-Approve-Execute protocol
    import_shared_tools :planning, visibility: "always"

    define_tool "generate_music_with_lyria", "Generate music with Google's Lyria 3. Default model lyria-3-pro-preview produces full songs (up to ~2-3 min) with vocals and lyrics when requested; lyria-3-clip-preview produces fast 30-second instrumental clips. Returns an MP3 (WAV for Pro) saved to the shared folder plus any generated lyrics." do
      parameter :prompt, "string", "The music description to generate from (English works best). Include genre, mood, instrumentation, tempo, and any lyrics for vocal tracks.", required: true
      parameter :lyria_model, "string", "Optional: 'pro' (default, full songs with optional vocals) or 'clip' (fast 30s instrumental).", required: false
      parameter :output_format, "string", "Optional: 'wav' for lossless audio (Pro model only; larger file) or 'mp3' (default).", required: false
      parameter :session, "object", "Session object (automatically provided). Carries any uploaded images for image-to-music.", required: false
    end
  end
end
